question:
Indicate which of the following is a linear combination of $A=\left[\begin{array}{rr}
      3& 2\\
			0 & 1 
    \end{array}\right]$, $B=\left[\begin{array}{rr}
      0& -1 \\
			1 & 2 
    \end{array}\right]$ and $C=\left[\begin{array}{rr}
      5& 4 \\
			-1 & 0
    \end{array}\right]$.

The spectral radius of the matrix  $A = \begin{bmatrix}
-3 &  1 \\
1 & -3 \end{bmatrix}$ is:

Which of the following vectors is an eigenvector of the matrix $A = \begin{bmatrix}
-3 & 1 \\
1 & -3 \end{bmatrix}$?

Let $A=\left( \begin{array}{rrr}
1 & -1 & 0 \\ 
0 & 1 & 1 \end{array}
\right)$  and $C=\left( \begin{array}{rr}
1  & 0 \\ 
2 & -1 \\
0  & 1 \end{array}
\right)$. Which of the following statements is correct?

Suppose that $A=\left( \begin{array}{rrr}
2 & 0 & -1 \\ 
3 & 1 & 0 \\ 
-2 & 1 & 3 \end{array}
\right)$.

Find matrix $B$ such that matrices $A$ and $B$ are inverses.
